(1, 'faq', 'Frequently Asked Questions', NULL, 'frontend', '<p>We are dedicated to providing you with a highly enjoyable&nbsp;and excellent service. Our top priority is to provide you with courteous, helpful service with any and all related questions. Please take a moment to review the frequently asked questions listed on this site. In most cases you''ll be able to resolve your problem quickly and easily through this site. Your happiness is our top priority! Below you''ll find some solutions to common problems using Xexposed.com&nbsp;You will find answers to most common and frequently asked questions on our FAQ page. Feel free to contact our customer live chat support with any other questions or concerns that we may not have answered for you here. it is in our best intrest to provide you with an immediate response.</p>\r\n<h2><a href="http://google.com">1 Payments</a></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3><a href="#">1.1 How can I add credits to my account?</a></h3>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">To add credits to your account, log in first. Once you have logged in, you can see the various payment options available in your country on your account page. You can choose the option that is most convenient for you.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2><a href="#">2 Your account</a></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>2.1 I forgot my login/password. How can I get them back?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Click on the ''forgot password'' on the homepage or on the login page. Enter your username or e-mail address in the box. Your login data will be sent to your mailbox. This may take a few minutes.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>2.2 How can I delete my account?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">You can deactivate your account by:<br />logging in to the websitego to ''my account'' on the bottom of the pageclick on ''cancel account''.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2><a href="#">3 Technical problems</a></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3.1 From which devices can I access your live video chat service?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">The live webcam platform and chat are supported on all PC or MAC devices with a good internet connectivity.<br />The only requirement is that your browser supports Flash.<br />On top of that our webcams are accessible via iPad or your 3G enabled mobile phone.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3.2 The video quality is very poor</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">The video stream of our webcammers are sent over the internet. The webcammer''s internet connection is therefore a determining factor for the quality of the video.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">The best thing to do in these cases is to report this to the webcammer. He/she can then try to correct the images or he/she will contact us to have a better image for your next private chat.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3.3 My webcam isn''t working</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Check whether your webcam is working in another application such as Skype or MSN.Click in the field where your webcam image should be with the right mouse button in the chat application. Choose settings / webcam icon and choose your webcam.Verify that no other program is using your webcam at the same timeIf the above mentioned steps don''t help, it''s best to reinstall your webcam''s driver software. This can always be found on the website of your webcam''s manufacturer.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3.4 My browser crashes all the time</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Your Adobe Flash player instalment is probably corrupt. You can solve this by reinstalling it.<br />You first need to remove the current version from your computer.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">To uninstall Adobe Flash Player, you need to follow Adobe''s instructions. These can be found here. You will need to download some things from the Adobe site.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Once the old version has been removed, you can install the new version, by taking the following steps:Follow the instructions on the Adobe siteOnce the have downloaded the latest version, close your browserInstall the update. You should then be able to see our webcams without any problems.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">For Windows VISTA users:<br />If the problem persists after reinstalling Flash, it could be caused by aMicrosoft Windows Vista permission problem.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Click on the Windows button and then the search function:<br />go to: C:\\Windows\\System32\\Macromed\\Flash\\right mouse click on the file: FlashUtil9b.exe or FlashUtil9e.exechoose ''Execute as Administrator'' and install the updateRestart your computer.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3.5 Loading preferences failed ... Probably firewall issue (port 1935). What do I need to do?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">The live webcam chat platform uses various ''ports'' of your internet connection.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">When these ports are blocked, you will not be able to make a connection with the webcammer. You can try to switch off your personal firewall (often a part of your anti-virus program). If you can then make a connection with our platform, then try to switch the firewall on again and explictly enable port 1935 and port 80 only.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Also check whether port 2037 and 1935 aren''t blocked by your operating system:<br />http://support.microsoft.com/kb/308127 (for PC)<br />http://homepage.mac.com/car1son/static_port_fwd_firewall.html (for MAC)</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">When you have switched off your firewall and it still doesn''t work, you can check whether you are using a ''router'' on your network. Firewalls could be configured on some routers that can block ports 1935 and 80. Check whether this is the case.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">If the above mentioned tips still don''t help, contact our live support.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3.6 The webcammer can''t hear me. What can I do?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">You can only talk with a webcammer while you are in a private session and your webcam has been switched on.<br />Your microphone is normally activated automatically. If you have connected several microphones (for example one in-built in the PC and one built into the webcam), you have to first determine (only once) within the application which microphone you want to use.<br />Right click in the chat window.You then get a menu, where you click on the option "Settings..."Your main screen becomes grey; you get the "Macromedia Flash Player Settings" menu (See below)Click below on the tab with the microphone, choose the microphone you want to activate in the drop-down list. Set the volume and check if "Reduce echo" is on.Click "close" to store and save your settings.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>3.7 I have problems accessing the video chat via my iPad</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">To have good access to our live webcams and chat it''s important that your device has a stable internet connection.<br />More information and a solution for the issue can be found on the support site of Apple via this link :<br />http://support.apple.com/kb/TS3237?viewlocale=en_US</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2><a href="#">4 Private chat</a></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>4.1 What is private chat?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Thanks to our private functionality you can get the webcammer entirely dedicated to you. As soon as you start the private session the other visitors will not be able to chat with the webcammer. On top of that you''ll be able to speak to the webcammer instead of typing.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">Some things you need to know about private sessions:<br />the webcammer decides if he/she offers private chat and at what price. The price is displayed in the button.private chat is only available for visitors with an account. Customers paying by telephone will not be able to use this service.when you start a private session, the webcammer will need to accept first. Sometimes it''s a good idea to ask the webcammer if he/she is prepared to offer you a special private show.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>4.2 Why I don''t see a private button?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">There can be several reasons:<br />The webcammer does not offer this functionality. Every webcammer can decide if they offer it or not. Request the webcammer to activate it.You are using your telephone to access our website. The private functionality is only available for visitors with an account. You can create an account in just a few seconds. Afterwards you can enjoy this function as well. The webcammer is already in an active private chat with another visitor. You can continue to watch the show until you wait for the current private session to end.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3>4.3 I can''t chat with the webcammer. Why?</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;">When a webcammer is in an active private session or starts a new one with another visitor, you will no longer be able to chat with him/her. You can of course continue to watch the live show.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2><a href="#">5 Contact Customer Service</a></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', 0, 1, NULL, ''),
