(25, 'safety', 'safety', NULL, 'backend', '<p>Condoms</p>\r\n<div class="content">\r\n<p>Certain materials like rubber toys are porous, so don''t be afraid to use a condom with them during your shows (you don''t need condoms for toys made out glass though). Chatters like to see a webcam model who uses condoms, it''s realistic and fun.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Toy Safety</p>\r\n<div class="content">\r\n<p>Do research and find out what the best care is for your toys and props. Improper toy care can lead to nasty infections, which keeps you from working. You should never work if your body isn''t healthy enough.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Play It Safe</p>\r\n<div class="content">\r\n<p>Last but not least, you should keep it safe! What good is making all that money if you start getting stalkers finding you outside of work? Never ever use the internet without using a router. They can be relatively cheap and will prove more priceless than you know. Average time to hack into someone''s unsecured computer is 16 minutes. You read that right, 16 minutes. If you are connected directly to your modem then your internet, computer and most importantly your personal information are not secure. The router creates a barrier that hackers cannot get through, especially if you have a secured password for wireless. You may only have one computer and don''t think you need a router because no one else is using your internet connection. No one else may be using it but if you don''t get a router and make a password for your wireless internet through your router your computer is at risk for Trojans and viruses that can jeopardize your safety. If you aren''t sure how to do this contact your router customer service and tell them you want to secure your internet access with a password. If you contact your internet provider they can''t do anything to secure your router. You need to call the customer service for your router. You can find their number on the box the router came in or look on line.</p>\r\n<p>Also equally if not more important is never to give out your personal information such as your real name, address, phone number or email to customers you meet while working, unless you know deep in your heart you have met the person you are going to marry :) It''s really not a joking matter because you never know what the person you are chatting with is really like, and what they are capable of. You are better off playing it safe, no matter how much you think you like them because your life isn''t worth the gamble!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 0, 1, NULL, NULL),
(26, 'general success manuel', 'general success manuel ', NULL, 'backend', '<p>Finding Webcam Jobs</p>\r\n<p>The website, network, or agency you work for makes a huge difference in your success or failure. Pick the right one, and you have a blast making more money than you ever thought was possible. Pick the wrong one, and you will waste tons of time without making money, and worse, you will feel discouraged with webcam modeling altogether. Your self confidence will suffer because you will assume it was all your fault, and you are not cut out to be a webcam model. You won''t even bother trying again, because everyone hates failure, especially more than once at doing the same thing!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>What Page You Will Appear On</p>\r\n<div class="content">\r\n<p>Even if you are on a very high traffic website, you may not see anyone in your room because you will be listed on a page noone sees. If you are not showcased on either page 1 or 2 under a popular category or the site''s home page, you might as well be on a site with no visitors, because that''s how you''ll feel. When looking for a webcam job, always ask how the site decides placement, and where you will be featured when you first start.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Working With An Agency</p>\r\n<div class="content">\r\n<p>There is a reason all successful Hollywood actors and actresses have agents. They have agents because they want to focus on doing what they know and do best, acting. They don''t have the time or desire to scout for auditions, negotiate pay and contracts, promote their image, do press releases, pick out potential scripts, discuss roles, projects, movies, etc.. They let their agents handle it all, why? Because that is what their agents know and do best, it''s their livelyhood. Agents have a direct incentive to find the best roles for their clients because the more money they get for their clients, the more money they will make for themselves, and the better their reputaion in the industry. If the agent does his/her job right, their clients will remain with them for their entire careers!</p>\r\n<p>Well, guess what, in the world of webcam modeling it works pretty much the same way. Webcam site owners work with modeling agencies to recruit models for their sites, and pay the agents directly for their services. The larger the agency, the more influence they have with the sites for model placement and hiring decisions. If you are a gorgeous, picture perfect model who is also a tough negotiator with sharp business skills and management contacts at top webcam sites, then you should not work with an agency, and try to apply directly with the largest sites you can find. You will most likely get hired, and join thousands of other hungry models in line to make a fortune in the business. Once you start working, if you don''t think you are making enough money or are not being promoted enough, tough luck! The site owners have no incentive to promote you because you''re on your own, and they are too busy making lots of money to care.</p>\r\n<p>Personally, I have always worked with an agency, and I have to say they were the key to my success from day one! I had a personal agent whom I could call on the phone day or night to ask for advice, report problems, or just share a few laughs about my day. Because of my agent, I was consistently showcased on the front page and the first page of my categories on the sites that I appeared on. I said sites because the agency I worked for,&nbsp;cam clients, represents many popular sites which get tons of traffic! Their system allowed me to work and be seen on thousands of websites at the same time. The amount of traffic, advice, and customers that I got by working with a top agency made it a no brainer for me, and I never looked back!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>traffic and quality</p>\r\n<p>Amount And Quality Of Traffic</p>\r\n<div class="content">\r\n<p>Perhaps the most important factor when deciding which website or network to work for is the amount of traffic they get. It''s not just the amount of traffic, but the type of trafic as well. Where is their traffic coming from? Are they just blindly buying text links on thousands of adult websites with low converting traffic, or is it a destination site itself with their own regular visitors and client base? Do they have U.S. traffic or if you are targeting another language or country, do they have your type of customers? These are the questions you need to ask, and don''t take their word for it, research it yourself. Look up the<a href="http://www.alexa.com/" target="_blank">Alexa</a>&nbsp;rating of the site(s) you are considering. Remember, any site with an Alexa rating of under 1,000,000 should not even be considered unless it''s a niche site like gay or shemale.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pick a name that is easy to remember.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Upload pictures of yourself to all 6 spots, preferably ones that grab members&rsquo; attention. Colorful, interesting, professional or half professional photos are a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Upload a teaser video of yourself</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 0, 0, NULL, NULL),
